import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='precipitation', by='location')
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('Precipitation')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation across the locations?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    yearly_data = data.groupby('year').agg({'temp_max': 'max', 'temp_min': 'min'})
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(yearly_data.index, yearly_data['temp_max'], label='Max Temperature')
    plt.plot(yearly_data.index, yearly_data['temp_min'], label='Min Temperature')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('How does the temperature vary across the years?')
    plt.legend()
    
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data.boxplot(column=['temp_max', 'temp_min'], by='location')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45 if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20 else 0)
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    weather_counts = data.groupby(['year', 'weather']).size().unstack().fillna(0)
    weather_counts.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.title("What is the most common weather condition across the years?")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
